AGI - In the middle of the day, at 14:00 local time, Israel will reunite the 'war cabinet' > for further evaluations on the topic of Israel's response to Iran.&nbsp; "The drones used against Israel are the same used in Ukraine, so it is too early to talk about de-escalation", warned the Israeli ambassador in Italy, Alon Bar, intervening Sky Tg24. The diplomat did not want to unbalance on an Israeli response attack. "I don't know," he said, "and I don't think it's a good idea to tell their enemies what we're going to do."&nbsp; "My country has continued Bar- has been attacked by hundreds of ballistic missiles and droni<br> but this is part of Iran's ongoing effort to lead to escalation in the region." From here, the consequence: "until we find a way to stop Iran this risk will remain."
&nbsp;
The ambassador also stressed the need to give "a stronger international response.> The Iranian Revolution Guard must be considered a terrorist organization."
&nbsp;
After Iran's attack on Israel, the Kremlin invited all Middle Eastern countries to moderation, and noted that "a further escalation does not benefit either of the two parties">.&nbsp;"We are extremely concerned about the escalation of tensions and we ask all countries in the region to exercise moderation. A further escalation is not in anyone's interest," said the press spokesman of the Kremlin Dmitry Peskov.&nbsp; "We will do everything in our power to avoid an escalation and convince Israel not to respond to the attack of Iran," said the French president, Emmanuel Macron. The leader of the Elysée also added that "Iran responded disproportionately to the Israeli attack in Damascus".

