But all that will happen in the classroom will flood media sites and social media. For at least four days a week Trump will attend the debate, which sees him charged with 34 crimes, > including forging financial documents to cover the black payment to the porn actress, whose real name is Stephanie Gregory Clifford.> Precisely this 45-year-old woman from Baton Rouge, Louisiana, stripper when she was still underage, awarded with the Avn Awards, the Oscars of the porn industry, protagonist in 2018 of a tour entitled "Make America Horny Again", recall of Trump's "Make America Great Again", but with porn connotations, will be the most anticipated by the court, the jurors, the media, but very feared by Trump, who last two months has banned everything.
&nbsp;
She, in fact, has already done so many times with some media, going down into details and painting a Trump in an unhonourable way, especially in contrast to the Machist narrative that the trumpians have married from the beginning. They were the same tycoon lawyers to admit, in their motion then rejected by the judge, that the "peelling detail" of the actress could harm the image of the former president. Trump has denied having ever had relations with Stormy, but he is sure that in these weeks the famous meeting took place in 2006 during a golf tournament will be unleashed.
&nbsp;
The pornstar told me she met the tycoon in Lake Tahoe. He invited her to dinner in his hotel's suite, then he showed her a copy of a golf magazine with his own printed cover image. "I told him - the actress told Cbs in 2018 - someone should take that magazine and shake you with that." "And at that point - he added - he had turned and had just lowered his pants a little. He had his underwear and I gave him a couple of taps."
&nbsp;
Daniels then told that Trump had asked her if she liked to participate in his TV show, "Celebrity Apprentice". L>ei had responded enthusiastically, and he told her: "Wow, you're special, you remind me of my daughter. You're smart and beautiful, I like you." Daniels had gone to the bathroom, and on the return he found Trump lying on the bed. "I reacted exactly where I ended up - he remembered - and I thought, well, let's go." According to his story, the two consumed sexual intercourse.
&nbsp;
The following year, Trump would call her on the phone, asking her to meet him at the Beverly Hills Hotel in Los Angeles, to discuss her participation in the TV show. On that occasion, tycoon would have asked her to have another relationship, but she declined the invitation. A month later he called her to tell her that it was not possible to insert her into the cast. This whole thing, according to the prosecution, had to remain secret, but she threatened to reveal everything in full electoral campaign.
&nbsp;
Trump would have bought his silence, giving her $130,000 through the all-round lawyer Michael Cohen.> On October 28, 2016, a few days before the election that tycoon would win, Stormy signed the confidentiality agreement. But then that pact was broken, the whole story came out, creating embarrassment. Also because at the time of their first meeting, Trump was already married to Melania for a year. In 2006, their son Barron was born. They are all particular that will be seen again often in the coming weeks.
&nbsp;
The Donald will sleep at Trump Tower on Fifth Avenue. The process will probably take a break on Wednesday, so tycoon can use this space to carry out its election campaign and participate in donation events. But it is almost certain that every day of the process will be used by Trump to launch his attacks. The staff would be working with some media friends to propagate his messages. All waiting for the great day: the one in which the former president of the United States should testify, as promised Friday during a press conference in Mar-a-Lago. "I will testify - he said - I will tell all the truth, and the truth is that nothing happened".
&nbsp;
He really had to testify, Trump will also have to submit to the prosecution's questions and this could open up new scenarios on the story. But at the same time it appears far away: first there will be the selection of jurors, a procedure that could last two weeks. There are hundreds of candidates. They will not be asked for political membership but will be asked questions about how they inform and about what media, whether they have worked in the past for Trump or participated in his fellowships and if they have ever been members of far-right militias like Proud Boys or have married the right-wing conspiracy theories of the QAnon movement. Among the witnesses expected in the classroom will be Hope Hicks, Trump's former assistant, who promises to provide details about what happened in the tycoon magic circle a few days before the 2016 elections.&nbsp;
